description: The Fourth Dimension is a location theorized by Bridget and Peter Quinn to be the ideal perfect world inhabited by peaceful beings. After they sent their son Ulysses (Neil Quin), to this dimension to escape the presumed doom of the Ulysses Research Center, the unidentified energy which saturated the dimension empower his human physiology. It was later revealed that the planet only maintains its peace by harvesting the inhabitants of other worlds to sustain its core.

deck: An island nation located in the Gulf of Mexico off the coast of Texas.
description: The nation of San Sebor was ran by the dictator El Fajita. The United States looked the other way as El Fajita tortured, persecuted and denied the basic liberties to the island nation's citizens all because El Fajita was an anti-Communist. With the uproar of LexCorp, and against the will of Claire Montgomery, the Conglomerate was used to overthrow the El Fajita's regime. The rebel leader El Carbonero was thrilled with the work of the Conglomerate and invited them back to the island when he is elected president.
